<p>copy into vim from GUI results missing line</p>
<ul>
  <li>before pasting to vim, make sure the Insert Mode is activated.</li>
  <li>the reason is that paste character <strong>i</strong> or character <strong>o</strong> will trigger
insert mode, and you will miss everying before</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="joining-two-lines-with-j">joining two lines with J</h4>
<ol>
  <li>J joins the line the cursor is on with the line below</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="open-file">open file</h4>

<ol>
  <li>vim -On file1 file2 nè¡¨ç¤ºè¦æ‰“å¼€çš„æ–‡ä»¶æ•°ï¼ŒOå¤§å†™è¡¨ç¤ºæ‰“å¼€å‚ç›´çª—å£</li>
  <li>open a new window below the current one
    <ul>
      <li>:new filename</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>open a new window beside the current one
    <ul>
      <li>:vert new filename</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

